experiences.detail:
Main responsibilities:
- Review and manage contracts, NDAs, agreements and other documents, etc.;
- Advise Managers for internal management and regulations;
- Make compliance checklists for Departments, standard contracts;
- Advise Managers and/or other Department for legal issues in operation; and
- Assist legal team leader in advising and making process of overseas investment.
Recognition and Gains: - Getting familiar with product development, manufacture and related issues.
- Setting up subsidiary overseas and settling operation issues.
- Knowing how to organize legal department's works and planning.

Main responsibilities:
- Prepare, review and manage supplier contract and other internal documents, decisions, etc.;
- Advise Managers and/or other Department for legal issues (i.e.: internal regulation; labour issues, etc.)
- Carry out licensing work (i.e.: business registration, license application, etc.) upon demand of operation;
- Prepare regular reports to authorities;
- Support in management of construction project/ manage construction documents; and
- Support in sales activities and control of sales contract.
Recognition and Gains: - Systematizing internal control/ contract management and system of regular report.
- Supporting departments for legal issues and difficulties/ disputes.

Main responsibilities:
- Review and manage supplier contract and other internal documents, decisions, etc.;
- Advise Managers and/or other Department for legal issues; and
- Carry out licensing work upon demand of operation.
Recognition and Gains: - Re-systematizing contracts for easy lookup;
- Creating standard form of contract for use.

Main responsibilities:
- Provide wide range of legal services and advice for mostly Korean investors;
- Provide advice on labor, investment, tax, foreign contractor withholding tax, construction, foreign loan regulation, foreign exchanges, etc.;
- Participate in dispute settlement process, i.e. joining negotiation meetings and meetings with authority for dispute settlement;
- Carry out licensing and post-licensing works for construction; work permit for foreign employees; and
- Draft and review contracts and other documents case by case.
Recognition and Gains: - Being familiar with Korean-culture business;
- Experienced in foreign investment related issued.

Main responsibilities:
- Advise on legal, regulatory and dispute resolution matters including company’s compliance with license scopes;
- Provide professional translation for clients’ documents;
- Monitor and update the legal provisions and regulatory related to enterprises, business, intellectual property, labour, etc.;
- Draft and review the clients' contracts and documents case by case;
- Review and take actions for debt recovery for clients; and
- Liaise with external parties including government agencies for proceeding the necessary legal procedures.
Recognition and Gains: - Being familiar with professional working environment.
- Gaining legal professional skills.
